#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:5
msgid "Layers"
msgstr "Calques"

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:7
msgid ""
"Grease Pencil sketches are organized in layers, much like the image layers "
"in the GIMP or Photoshop\\ :sup:`®`\\ . These layers are not related to any "
"of the other layer systems in Blender."
msgstr ""
"Les esquisses au crayon gras sont organisées sur des calques, les calques "
"d'images dans GIMP ou Photoshop\\ :sup:`®`\\ . Ces calques ne sont en lien "
"avec aucun autre système de calques dans Blender."

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:11
msgid ""
"The layers' main purpose is to gather sketches that are related in some "
"meaningful way (i.e. \"blocking notes\", \"director's comments on blocking"
"\", or \"guidelines\"). For this reason, all the strokes on a layer (not "
"just those made after a particular change) are affected by that layer's "
"color, opacity, and stroke thickness settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:16
msgid ""
"Layers are managed in the *Grease Pencil Panel* of the *Properties region* :"
"kbd:`N` shown here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:21
msgid "Grease Pencil Panel."
msgstr "Panneau du crayon gras."

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:23
msgid ""
"Use the adjacent controls to Add, Remove or adjust the position of a layer "
"in the list. Each layer has a visibility icon, and a lock icon to protect it "
"from further changes. Double click on a layer name to rename it."
msgstr ""
"Utilisez les contrôles adjacents à Add, Remove ou ajustez la position du "
"calque dans la liste. Chaque calque possède un icône de visibilité, et un "
"icône de verrou pour le protéger des modifications ultérieures. Double-"
"cliquez sur un nom de calque pour le renommer.  "

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:27
msgid ""
"There is a list of layers attached to each scene and a list of layers "
"associated with each object. The buttons above the list box control its "
"contents, showing either the layers associated with the active scene or the "
"list of layers associated with the active object."
msgstr ""
"Il existe une liste de calques attachés à chaque scène et une liste de "
"calques associés à chaque objet. Les boutons au dessus de la boîte liste "
"contrôle son contenu, en montrant soit les calques associés à la scène "
"active soit la liste de calques associés à l'objet actif. "

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:32
msgid ""
"By default, most operations occur only on the *active* layer highlighted in "
"the list."
msgstr ""
"Par défaut, la plupart des opérations se passent uniquement sur le calque "
"*actif* surligné dans la liste."

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:36
msgid "Animating Sketches"
msgstr "Animation des esquisses"

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:38
msgid ""
"Use the Grease Pencil to do basic pencil tests (i.e. 2D animation in "
"flipbook style). Sketches are stored on the frame that they were drawn on, "
"as a separate drawing (only on the layer that they exist on). Each drawing "
"is visible until the next drawing for that layer is encountered. The only "
"exception to this is the first drawing for a layer, which will also be "
"visible before the frame it was drawn on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:45
msgid ""
"Therefore, it is simple to make a pencil-test/series of animated sketches:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:47
msgid "Go to first relevant frame. Draw."
msgstr "Allez à la première frame relevante. Dessinez."

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:48
msgid "Jump to next relevant frame. Draw some more."
msgstr "Sautez à la frame relevante suivante. Dessinez un peu plus."

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:49
msgid ""
"Keep repeating process, and drawing until satisfied. Voila! Animated "
"sketches."
msgstr ""
"Répétez la procédure, et dessinez jusqu'à satisfaction. Voilà ! des "
"esquisses animées."

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:53
msgid "Onion Skinning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:59
msgid "Grease Pencil Onion Skinning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:61
msgid ""
"Onion-skinning, also known as ghosting, helps an animator by displaying the "
"neighboring frames as a faded trail. Enable the option with the *Onion Skin* "
"button in the grease pencil properties region (see :ref:`fig-gp-onion` shown "
"above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/grease_pencil/layers_and_animation.rst:65
msgid ""
"Use *Before* and *After* to set the number of ghost frames drawn on either "
"side of the current frame. When *Use Custom Colors* (Marked *A*) is enabled, "
"you can also use the *Before* and *After* controls to change the color of "
"the ghosted frames."
msgstr ""

